The paper discusses the problem of emotion processing in Human-Computer Interaction, which is a topic that falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also focuses on multimedia documents such as text, images, sounds, and videos, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). The use of physiological signals to estimate emotion also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of affective computer interfaces and video-on-demand, which could fall under the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
